name: AMO
overview: Despite the Philippine government's crackdown on narcotics, high schooler Joseph expands his drug running while his cop uncle profits from corruption.

episodes.name: The Runner
episodes.overview: After receiving a text message, high school student Joseph sneaks out of class to take care of some risky business in a local neighborhood.

episodes.name: The Officer
episodes.overview: When Joseph's name appears on a suspects list kept by the police as part of a government crackdown on drug offenders, his Uncle Camilo takes action.

episodes.name: The Traitor
episodes.overview: When Joseph spots a fellow gang member in suspicious company, he secretly follows him and witnesses a horrifying betrayal.

episodes.name: The Execution
episodes.overview: In the middle of the night, Joseph sneaks out of his family's home to join his gang in seeking revenge against the traitor in their midst.

episodes.name: The Cheater
episodes.overview: While visiting his sister in Manila, Joseph has another run-in with the law. His brother-in-law pulls some strings but makes his wife suspicious.

episodes.name: The Drug
episodes.overview: As the extent of his double life unfolds, brother-in-law Bino introduces Joseph to the world of high-end party drugs.

episodes.name: The Party
episodes.overview: Joseph enjoys his increased income, but the glamour of his new job is soon tarnished by a TV news report and an undercover operation.

episodes.name: The Operation
episodes.overview: Bino tries to help Joseph and gang mate Tisoy cover their tracks. But the police are hot on their heels and determined to catch them, dead or alive.

episodes.name: The Asset
episodes.overview: Police officer Rod joins colleague Camilo on a mission to capture a Japanese drug lord, using sex worker Christina as their undercover asset.

episodes.name: The Kidnap
episodes.overview: With Christina's help, Rod and Camilo raid Takeo's home and make an arrest. But it soon becomes apparent that this is no ordinary police capture.

episodes.name: The Cover-up
episodes.overview: When the press start asking questions about an alleged kidnapping of a Japanese national, Camilo and Rod are ordered to cover their tracks.

episodes.name: The Whistleblower
episodes.overview: Rod gets greedy and insists on going after the additional money they were promised, unaware Takeo's wife is working with a different police unit.

episodes.name: The Escape
episodes.overview: Camilo goes into hiding and calls his boss, begging for help. Meanwhile, a witness comes forward and spills details of the kidnapping on a radio show.
